The article is a letter from Raul Castro, the President of Cuba, to Barack Obama, the President of the United States. In the letter, Castro confirms that Cuba has agreed to re-establish diplomatic relations with the United States and open permanent diplomatic missions in both countries on July 20, 2015. Cuba is motivated by the desire to develop respectful and cooperative relations with the US, based on the principles of equality, peaceful dispute settlement, non-interference in domestic matters, and respect for human rights and fundamental freedoms. The letter also references the Vienna Convention on Diplomatic Relations and the Vienna Convention on Consular Relations, which will govern diplomatic and consular relations between Cuba and the United States. Castro expresses his consideration and regards to President Obama.